# GraveCareUkraine.com

Live site: https://gravecareuakraine.com  
Netlify preview: https://superlative-dragon-986bcd.netlify.app  
GitHub repo: https://github.com/GCUkraine/GraveCareUkraine.com

---

## How the site works

```
You edit index.html (on GitHub or locally)
        ↓
Commit to main branch
        ↓
Netlify auto-detects the commit
        ↓
Site is live in ~45 seconds
```

No build step. No scripts. index.html IS the website.

---

## Files

```
index.html      ← THE WEBSITE — edit this to change anything
success.html    ← Page shown after order form is submitted
README.md       ← This file
.gitignore      ← Keeps junk files (.DS_Store etc) off GitHub
```

---

## How to edit content

### Option A — GitHub browser (recommended, works on phone)
1. Go to: https://github.com/GCUkraine/GraveCareUkraine.com/edit/main/index.html
2. Make your changes
3. Click "Commit changes" → "Commit directly to main" → green button
4. Wait 45 seconds → site is updated. Bookmark that URL.

### Option B — Local editor (VS Code etc.)
```bash
git pull
# edit index.html
git add index.html
git commit -m "describe what you changed"
git push
```

### Option C — Ask Claude
Paste the section you want changed and describe what you want.
Claude edits it and gives you the updated block to paste in.

---

## What to edit — use Ctrl+F to find these in index.html

| What | Search for |
|---|---|
| WhatsApp number | wa.me/ |
| Email address | mailto: |
| Hero headline | You are far away |
| Hero subtext | We care for the graves |
| Stats (1000+, 17yr, 16 cities) | stat-num |
| Service names/prices | service-name |
| Testimonials | testimonial-text |
| Cities list | city-tag |
| Guarantee text | Our guarantee |

---

## Order form — setup & notifications

Form uses Netlify Forms (free, 100 submissions/month).

### Activate (one-time)
Submit a test order on the live site → go to Netlify dashboard → Forms tab → order-request appears.

### Email notifications on every order
Netlify → Forms → order-request → Form notifications → Add notification → Email notification → enter your email → Save.

### See all submissions
Netlify dashboard → Forms → order-request.

### Optional: Zapier → WhatsApp/Gmail alert (free, 100/month)
Trigger: Netlify → New Form Submission (order-request)
Action: Gmail → Send email to yourself

---

## Delete a file from GitHub

Browser: open file → trash icon → Commit changes

Terminal:
```bash
git rm filename
git commit -m "remove filename"
git push
```

## Remove .DS_Store already on GitHub
```bash
git rm --cached .DS_Store
git commit -m "Remove .DS_Store"
git push
```

---

## Connect domain (one-time)
1. Netlify → Site configuration → Domain management → Add custom domain → gravecareuakraine.com
2. At Namecheap add:
   - A record: @ → 75.2.60.5
   - CNAME: www → superlative-dragon-986bcd.netlify.app
3. SSL activates automatically

